						<summary>

						<p>Pillar set up behind the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>BOLLAYA REḌḌI (?).</p>						

						<p>1286 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The inscription is dated in Śaka 1208, Vyaya, corresponding to 1286 A.D. records the gift of land after obtaining it on <hi rend="italic">pullari</hi> and <hi rend="italic">tīru</hi> lease from the king by Sarvēśvarayyaṅgāru who accompained by local Brahmarājimayyaladēva to certain Mahādēva for the maintenance of feeding house <hi rend="italic">(satramu)</hi> at Alaṁpura.</p>						

						</summary>
